Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Covigo’s award-winning software enables operators and enterprises to develop and deploy mobile, web and portal applications rapidly and cost-effectively. Covigo software was created from the ground up with ROI and TCO as primary objectives. The product suites provided by Covigo are: Covigo Mobility Suite for Enterprises: Today’s business environment is forcing companies with a strategic focus on their field operations to eliminate inefficient process costs, improve customer and supplier relationships, and decrease working capital deployed in the field. Covigo’ Mobility Suite for Enterprises enables organizations to rapidly develop and deploy offline and online applications to laptops, PDAs and smart phones. End-users can continue working without having to rely on live network connectivity. Covigo software also delivers alerts to users based on events taking place within the business systems. Covigo Mobility Suite for Operators: The decline in voice revenue and ARPU is compelling operators to move swiftly to roll out rich wireless data services to their subscribers. Covigo Mobility Suite for Operators enables operators and application developers to reduce services rollout time & cost by up to 80%, optimize services through business analytics, and involve third-party application developers. Covigo software enables operators and service providers to rapidly create and deliver adaptive user interfaces that are optimized for multiple types of devices, including WAP phones and PDAs of all kinds. Operators can target subscribers using browser-based and alerts-based services. Covigo Portal Enhancement Suite: Portal software enables enterprises to provide their employees, customers and partners with a one-stop personalized view into business processes, applications and information. Covigo’s Portal Enhancement solution enables enterprises to design, build and test portal applications within days and deploy them on portal server software from market-leading vendors. Covigo software includes a visual programming environment that enables rapid development of portlets to run on industry-leading portal servers. In addition to enabling pro-active notifications from portal applications, Covigo enables portal applications to be taken offline to run on laptops and PDAs.

Description: The Rocket Racing League is takes the excitement of Indy Car Racing into the space age. Founded by Granger Whitelaw and Peter Diamandis,
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Rocket Racing is super cool. Think NASCAR, Indy Car or Formula One racing in the sky, using rocket-powered aircraft flown by Top Gun pilots and astronauts. It’s the closest thing to Star Wars Pod Racing here on Earth. For the thousands of fans on-site, as well as millions at home, the Rocket Racing League® will transform 21st Century racing as they know it. To be held at venues across the country, RRL will feature multiple rocket races, from closed circuit to drag-style racing, pitting 2 to 10 Rocket Racer® aircraft roaring head-to-head for victory. The closed circuit format is planned to be a 4-lap, multiple elimination heat on a 5-mile Formula One-style Raceway-In-The-Sky™. The drag style race will feature two Rocket Racers soaring in tandem just 20 feet apart. The future of RRL will include multiple airframes and propulsion systems to develop the X-Racers. Currently, RRL is using a Velocity airframe and a single-thrust liquid oxygen (LOX) and ethanol rocket engine developed by Armadillo Aerospace, led by John Carmack (Doom and Quake). Unlike a jet engine that burns oxygen from the atmosphere as its oxidizer, the X-Racer, flying at 300 mph, carries its own oxidizer in the form of liquid oxygen.

Description: Newman Machine Company is a manufacturers of woodworking machinery.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Newman Machine Company is a manufacturers of woodworking machinery. Over a century ago, in 1907, George F. Newman, the co-founder and first president of Newman Machine Company, had a far-sighted vision of the importance of machines in the lumber, millwork, and furniture industries.  The first machine developed by the company was a lathe mill and bolter, which served the need for volume production of wood lathes used extensively at that time, and the demand for this machine launched the small company on the road to success. Shortly thereafter, a four-sided planer and matcher, the No. 8, was designed for the small lumber plants. This machine and improved models of it were installed in over 978 small planing mills starting in 1910. In 1912 the company designed and built the first of its larger planers and matchers, the No. 97. Acceptance of this machine was so great that additional facilities were needed. After World War I the company designed and built what is thought to be the industry’s first planer and matcher with ball bearings. It was sold to Cox Lumber Company of Wadesboro, North Carolina. Newman’s production of its ball bearing planers and matchers was a forerunner of one of the most important changes in the woodworking industry – the transition from plain or Babbitt bearings to ball bearings. Continuing in this leadership, the company in the early 1920’s designed its complete line of machines with ball bearings, giving its customers faster, trouble-free machines, adaptable to quicker adjustments and providing a better finish to raise the quality of their products. All of this resulted in increased quality and in cost savings to the woodworking industry. In 1926 the company created two models of the most modern direct motor driven electric molders of the time. By 1934 the company had expanded and positioned itself doing good work in woodworking equipment. It continued on a path of growth and innovation which only slowed as a result of the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor. Newman manufactured woodworking machinery almost entirely for the armed services throughout the World War II years. When peace came in 1945 Newman Machine Company was extremely busy supplying the needs of the woodworking industry. Over the next 15 years more than 5,000 heavy-duty woodworking machines were built.

Description: The Intelligent Community Forum is a global network of cities and regions with a think tank at its center.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Intelligent Community Forum (ICF) is a global network of cities and regions with a think tank at its center that studies how intelligent communities use ICT to succeed in the broadband economy. It seeks to share the best practices of the world’s intelligent communities in adapting to the demands of the broadband economy, conducts research, creates conference content, offers educational and advisory services, establishes institutes, and presents annual awards. Using evidence-based research, the ICF offers guidance through reports, books, live and online educational programs, and conferences. Its programs aim to help communities adapt to the demands of the broadband economy and build sustainable economies. Its programs include Community Accelerator, Center of Excellence, and Annual Summit. The ICF Foundation is the nonprofit membership association of the Intelligent Community Forum. Its members are communities honored by the Forum’s international awards program for intelligent communities, which use information and communications technology to grow prosperous, inclusive, sustainable economies. Brain Gain, Seeking Our Destiny, Broadband Economies, Future Cities, and The Safe City are some of the books published by the ICF. It also publishes reports and white papers. Each year, the ICF presents an awards program for intelligent communities and the public-sector and private-sector partners who contribute to them. Its award programs include The Smart21, The Top7 Intelligent Communities, Intelligent Community Visionary of the Year, Intelligent Community of the Year , and Founders Award. The Intelligent Community Forum is operated from New York, United States.
Founders: John Jung, Louis Zacharilla, Robert Bell

Description: Lifetime is an American cable and satellite television channel that is part of Lifetime Entertainment Services.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Lifetime Television is a premiere entertainment destination for all women, focused on offering a range of original programming, including scripted and non-fiction series as well as movies. Along with Lifetime Movies, Lifetime Real Women and Lifetime Digital, Lifetime Television is part of Lifetime Entertainment Services, LLC, which is a subsidiary company of A+E Networks. A+E Networks’s associated brands include A&E, HISTORY, Lifetime, LMN, FYI, and Vice TV, and it is a joint venture between Disney-ABC Television Group and Hearst Corporation. Lifetime Television seeks to create content that understands, empathizes and showcases women and women’s issues. In the 1980s, Daytime from Hearst-ABC Video Services, also referred to as BETA, curated content for women as a cable service. Additionally, the channel Cable Health Network produced health-focused media. These proved to be Lifetime Television’s creative inspiration. In 1984, Lifetime was created after Hearst/ABC’s Daytime and Viacom’s Cable Health Network partnered up. In its early days, Lifetime aired talk shows, call-in-programs and medical information.  Lifetime Television now produces made-for-TV films, reality series, second-run syndicated series, feature films and made-for-television films. It also provides broadcast coverage, HD simulcast and international programming. Some of Lifetime Television’s main goals center around corporate responsibility to create equal opportunities for female professionals in the entertainment industry and to support different female communities. These actions include Lifetime’s Stop Breast Cancer for Life, Broader Focus, #SheDidThat, Her America series, History Herstory series, Lifetime Real Women Network, SheReports newsletter and Stop Violence Against Women campaign. Lifetime Television is headquartered in New York, New York, and operates in more than 110 territories across the globe.
